<taxonomicName id="572556D2A4A8423EEE11FC84A21B142E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Zygophyllaceae" genus="Larrea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Larrea tridentata" order="Zygophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tridentata">Larrea tridentata</taxonomicName>
(DC.) Coville.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E8FBE1DDC26E8C91E81541FE820F1BB3" pageId="9" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F090DF69CCFDF47847B545499400191D" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA2F063509CCD25C7D3E1AA0E99A0A8F" pageId="9" pageNumber="96">
This species is the best known of the 
<taxonomicName id="C2A11A78F0C082338F18C6426EBFEEF4" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Townsendiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Townsendiella" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Townsendiella</taxonomicName>
, given the extensive life history work conducted on it and its host (
<bibRefCitation id="2F040BF80D34E6947897000E6B72F571" author="Rozen, JG Jr" journalOrPublisher="American Museum Novitates" pageId="14" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 11" title="Biology and larvae of the cleptoparasitic bee Townsendiellapulchra and nesting biology of its host Hesperapislarreae (Hymenoptera: Apoidea)." volume="3005" year="1991">Rozen and McGinley 1991</bibRefCitation>
). It will be interesting to see if all 
<taxonomicName id="6998BA7D9A20F38D09CD650DC2634165" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Townsendiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Townsendiella" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Townsendiella</taxonomicName>
share similar life histories, once such information becomes available for the remaining species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
